name: First Parish Church Congregational UCC
directions: Looking at the front of the building, off to the left and set back from the building facade is a small art gallery that has a handicap accessible ramp in front of it. Go through the glass door(s) into the gallery. At the back of the gallery on the right hand side, is a set of doors leading into the church proper. Go through those doors and the bathroom is immediately off to the left.
comment: Male/female handicap signed bathroom that is single occupancy and VERY large and clean. Door handle has a push button lock. There's a big window looking back over some buildings, but you can do your business without being on display. It's a church, but the sign out front says 'open and affirming.' Freeport's also a shopping outlet town so they're used to people needing a restroom.

name: Rachel Carson National Wildlife Refuge
directions: From the parking area, go towards the trailhead; the bathroom building is off to the left.
comment: The bathroom building has two male/female signed single occupancy rooms that are handicap accessible. These are so-called 'primitive' restrooms with a stainless steel composting toilet - basically a large pipe with a seat coming out of the floor - and sanitizer but no sink or mirror. As far as this type goes, this one is the best and cleanest one I've ever seen (and I've seen/smelled/used some BAD ones!). Only available during daylight hours.

comment: May be subject to College hours (you do not have to be a student to enter the building).
